      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's a fair breakdown, but honestly it feels like you're giving both sides equal weight just to be safe. if you actually look at most modern ethical consensus, isn't the 'national security' argument usually just a way to mask xenophobia or prioritize property/borders over actual human lives? like, isn't it harder to make a serious, non-biased moral case for stopping someone from escaping death than it is to defend a line on a map?",
